=== Lists ===

''Bullet lists'' can be written by putting one ore more asterix (*) at
the beginning of a line. Multiple asterisks means ''nesting'':

<pre>
* First item
** A sub item
** Other sub item
*** One more deeper
* Second item
* ...
</pre>

produces the following output:

* First item
** A sub item
** Other sub item
*** One more deeper
* Second item
* ...

Similarly, using the hash character (#) creates ''numbered lists'':

<pre>
# First item
## A sub item
## Other sub item
### One more deeper
# Second item
# ...
</pre>

will give the following output:

# First item
## A sub item
## Other sub item
### One more deeper
# Second item
# ...

It is possible to create ''definition lists'':

<pre>
;item 1
: definition 1
;item 2
: definition 2-1
: definition 2-2
</pre>

produces

;item 1
: definition 1
;item 2
: definition 2-1
: definition 2-2

